}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== {{On at76c50x matrix}}
There are multiple revisions and sub-models of this device.
CompUSA sold one CNUSB-611 submodel (OUI: 00:08:A1, ID: 1371:5743), which, according to the USB ID repository is a CNUSB-611 (D).
"05-01-0485-00" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
Models with the CNet VID specified by the USB ID repository are.. *1371:0001 CNet Technology Inc. CNUSB-611AR Wireless Adapter-G [AT76C503] *1371:0002 CNet Technology Inc. CNUSB-611AR Wireless Adapter-G [AT76C503] (FiberLine WL-240U) *1371:0013 CNet Technology Inc. CNUSB-611 Wireless Adapter [AT76C505] *1371:0014 CNet Technology Inc. CNUSB-611 Wireless Adapter [AT76C505] (FiberLine WL-240U) **this model appears to be the [[CNet CNUSB-611G]] *1371:5743 CNet Technology Inc. CNUSB-611 (D) Wireless Adapter [AT76C503]
The AT76C502/3/5A device matrix also specifies that the device has a default Atmel ID (03eb:7603)..
"05-01-0485-00" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
